The desired hospital room call bell system was implemented successfully with the help of 
tranistors , timerIC, buzzer and LED. The circuit works as required. When the push button is 
pressed it activates the buzzer and LEDs. The system is active until the reset button is 
acitivated. The same circuit is made for two rooms – emergency and regular, where the 
emergency room is given more priority. The capacitor based timing control prevents 
continuous ringing and operates the bell for certain period of time. The timing parameters of 
the circuit were calculated and verified using MULTISIM software.The priority mechanism 
using diode logic was also tested, when both the buttons are pressed simulatanously only the 
buzzer of the emergency room becomes on and the buzzer of the normal room is not activated 
due to the diode operation. 
